com.gracenote.gnsdk
Class GnAudioFile

java.lang.Object
  com.gracenote.gnsdk.GnAudioFile
All Implemented Interfaces:
IGnAudioSource
public class GnAudioFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements IGnAudioSource

Provides a means to read an audio file and return data as raw PCM. WAV file decoding is supported natively. AAC and MP3 are supported for devices running Android API 16 or above. This is a Gracenote helper delegate class to extract raw audio from encoded audio files. It can be used by GNSDK to generate MusicID-File fingerprints. For all helper delegate classes you can provide your own implementation, it just needs to implement the correct interface, in this case IGnAudioSource. If you do provide your own implementation Gracenote recommends starting with this implementation and altering as required; therefore the source is available on request. Safe Mode GnAudioFile runs in safe mode by default. Safe mode takes extra steps to detect audio files that will cause a crash in Android's native audio decoders (such as some ALAC files when decoded on some devices). Running in safe mode reduces performance and you are encouraged to turn safe mode off if running on a device build proven to not exhibit such decoding crashes. Unfortunately testing all audio format and Android device variations is not feasible, so you should determine if the scope of your application can narrow those variantions, and if so turn off safe mode if no Android decoder crashes are found.
